{"TopicId":145282,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"Devnotes Tuesday:\u00A0Two sprints down, one to go!","CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T23:37:21Z","PageNum":8,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Castille7","CreatedById":101668,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T19:22:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuge thanks to Squad for all the details going into this fasinating game, your hard work is very much appreciated!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoverDude","CreatedById":105198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T19:22:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705510\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470402228\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have some more, more specific questions for \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022105198\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RoverDude\u003C/a\u003E \u003C/span\u003E:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Set DSN to 0\u0022 - where are science reports received in this case? Is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E the last receiving link in the chain and will it work similar to a rover on any other body regarding occlusion?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpeaking of which: occlusion is being included I remember, but simplified - so every body is seen as a perfect sphere I guess, mountains not hindering the signal?\u003Cbr\u003E\n(What about places below \u0022sea level\u0022 of the body though?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLoss of signal will impair control - in which way exactly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Somehow my phone did not show me the last posts in this thread. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo, DSN can only be completely deactivated and will have to be replaced by a mod - no simple reducing communications to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. \u00A0Up to the mod you\u0027re replacing it with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. \u00A0With soft occlusion (and no\u00A0raytracing) mountains will not occlude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. \u00A0Loss of signal limits your control options.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. \u00A0You can adjust the DSN range multiplier. \u00A0To disable it entirely, just set it to zero.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470422119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147002\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022beelzerob\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, beelzerob said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt won\u0027t be like remote tech. \u00A0You\u0027ll never completely lose signal with a probe, but you\u0027ll instead have \u0022degraded\u0022 control when there is no signal path. \u00A0My guess would be something like the throttle only goes to full on or full off until signal is restored. \u00A0Also, no signal delay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this, yes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbMav","CreatedById":70338,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T19:30:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470424979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can adjust the DSN range multiplier. \u00A0To disable it entirely, just set it to zero.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRange being calculated from Kerbin\u0027s core?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what would be the setting to limit myself to reception at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E (or in other words to ground level, requiring the manual building of a receiving station)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:32:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470419260\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NathanKell\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, NathanKell said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E Autostruts won\u0027t restrut unless the vessel is modified, so probably what happened was they were still strutting that tank _despite_ it being light now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHm. It was probably what I thought at the time then - ridiculously high \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E because the transfer stage was quite large and quite empty when the problem started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"brusura","CreatedById":57899,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:43:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470422119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147002\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022beelzerob\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, beelzerob said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt won\u0027t be like remote tech. \u00A0You\u0027ll never completely lose signal with a probe, but you\u0027ll instead have \u0022degraded\u0022 control when there is no signal path. \u00A0My guess would be something like the throttle only goes to full on or full off until signal is restored. \u00A0Also, no signal delay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470424979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this, yes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is very unfortunate, the ability to execute a maneuver node planned before the signal blackout is the foundation stone of mission without pilot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-05T20:43:53Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2016 08:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by brusura\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:53:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705988\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470425458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what would be the setting to limit myself to reception at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (or in other words to ground level, requiring the manual building of a receiving station)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n600km \u002B ... 75m or so. \u00A0Make it 601km for a greater range of ground stations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-05T20:55:58Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2016 08:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbMav","CreatedById":70338,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:55:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706094\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470430415\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022regex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, regex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n600km \u002B ... 75m or so. \u00A0Make it 601km to avoid decimals.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would have been my guess, had he not said \u0022range multiplier\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470429787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022brusura\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, brusura said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is very unfortunate, the ability to execute a maneuver node planned before the signal blackout is the foundation stone of mission without pilot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can plan at least one node and let the probecore aim at it (as long as \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is not turned off on signal loss) before loss of signal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:57:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWant to quickly point out that in one of the first ever dev blogs, it was said that development takes place in the form of \u0022Sprints\u0022, with the plan that every 3-4 weeks there would be another stable release. Judging by the title of this weeks post, you can VERY VAGUELY judge\u00A0that 1.2 may drop in 3-4 weeks. Please do not quote me on this though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T20:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706097\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470430553\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would have been my guess, had he not said \u0022range multiplier\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen you just have to wait for the update to figure out how to adjust the multiplier, and it shouldn\u0027t be hard to figure out.. \u00A0I\u00A0mean, we\u0027re all playing this guessing game at feature specifics when the devs clearly don\u0027t want to give specifics right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"brusura","CreatedById":57899,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T21:13:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470424979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this, yes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure....\u00A0I guess we will have to wait to see what kind of limited action we could take once the signal is lost\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T21:32:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nITT: Fretting about things we don\u0027t have enough information about to make reasonable assumptions, therefore assuming the absolute worst. Oh, and a heaping helping of inability to just wait and see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T21:46:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706152\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470432767\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nITT: Fretting about things we don\u0027t have enough information about to make reasonable assumptions, therefore assuming the absolute worst. Oh, and a heaping helping of inability to just wait and see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHush you infidelly sane you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUncontrolled fretting and intense debate about possible changes without any access to actual facts is our divine right as forum users!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr at least we can whine over how possible additions to the game might destroy our gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T22:13:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706172\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470433601\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr at least we can whine over how possible additions to the game might destroy our gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe drank all that whine after 1.0 came out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Northstar1989","CreatedById":91005,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-05T22:32:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo glad to see work being done on the optimization front! \u00A0I\u0027ve been taking a break from KSP for a good while because the performance in some of the latest versions has been simply unplayable on my already weak laptop- but totally looking forward to loading KSP back up again come this update! \u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoverDude","CreatedById":105198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T02:45:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705988\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470425458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRange being calculated from Kerbin\u0027s core?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what would be the setting to limit myself to reception at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (or in other words to ground level, requiring the manual building of a receiving station)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin\u0027s diameter is already worked in. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0111narwhalz","CreatedById":110660,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T05:30:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470451517\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoverDude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RoverDude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin\u0027s diameter is already worked in. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the setting is 0 for this usecase? Or 1? Or whatever the default is?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jasper_f","CreatedById":106885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T09:09:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222705988\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470425458\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRange being calculated from Kerbin\u0027s core?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what would be the setting to limit myself to reception at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (or in other words to ground level, requiring the manual building of a receiving station)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is what I originally understood from the squadcast mentioned earlier (which appears to not be the case). At first I tried to simulate this with AntennaRange. However, limiting Kerbin\u0027s range to a certain altitude involves all of Kerbin; not just the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. Hence you can have a working connection when you\u0027re at one of the poles as long as you\u0027re below this maximum altitude, even without a satellite network. I have now made a custom profile in RemoteTech that I think combines the different mechanisms from RemoteTech and the upcoming stock telemetry system. I use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E as default, and only use the stock antenna\u0027s that now only have omnidirectional capabilities. This way I can simulate having a required tracking station at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and build my own network on top of this. Hopefully I will be able to easily replace RemoteTech with the stock telemetry system, or disable telemetry and happily keep using RemoteTech. Either way, I am happy with this setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Navy2k","CreatedById":95246,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T17:35:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222702941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470238226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3.8.2016 at 5:30 PM, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust back up that install and continue to use it until your mods update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222702979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470239960\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3.8.2016 at 5:59 PM, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor every person enjoying 1.1.x, there seems to be a person still waiting on a playable Unity 5 version of KSP.\u00A0 If Squad delayed 1.2 any more than absolutely necessary there likely would be a pitchfork mob.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/564x/82/e0/74/82e07402c94674dab1761ed5cba76725.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002282e07402c94674dab1761ed5cba76725.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhereAmI","CreatedById":165309,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T18:03:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing that worries me about the auto strutting is that it might affect the spacecraft exchange scene. The ship that uses auto strutting may no longer be stable without auto strutting, that means all the people who want to share their crafts will have to specify if they use auto strutting or not. And since the data about auto strutting is most likely not preserved in the craft save file, you\u0027ll also have to manually enable auto strutting every time you want to use someone else\u0027s ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-06T18:04:39Z\u0022 title=\u002208/06/2016 06:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 6, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by WhereAmI\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0111narwhalz","CreatedById":110660,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T19:06:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222707181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470506636\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165309\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhereAmI\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, WhereAmI said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing that worries me about the auto strutting is that it might affect the spacecraft exchange scene. The ship that uses auto strutting may no longer be stable without auto strutting, that means all the people who want to share their crafts will have to specify if they use auto strutting or not. And since the data about auto strutting is most likely not preserved in the craft save file, you\u0027ll also have to manually enable auto strutting every time you want to use someone else\u0027s ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t expect this issue to arise. Autostrutting is intrinsic to the .craft. Only the\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eoption\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0to toggle autostruts per-part is dependent upon difficulty (I assume) settings. Once a part is autostrutting, or not, the user can turn off the Advanced Tweakables option, and the part\u0027s individual setting will persist (assuming, of course, that a save was applied).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T19:28:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222707181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470506636\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165309\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhereAmI\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, WhereAmI said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing that worries me about the auto strutting is that it might affect the spacecraft exchange scene. The ship that uses auto strutting may no longer be stable without auto strutting, that means all the people who want to share their crafts will have to specify if they use auto strutting or not. And since the data about auto strutting is most likely not preserved in the craft save file, you\u0027ll also have to manually enable auto strutting every time you want to use someone else\u0027s ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t assume autostrutting is not in the .craft file, in act I\u0027d assume the opposite. And if it is, this is no different than thrust limiting or any other \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E-tweakable thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T20:17:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222702101\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470181041\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266485\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SQUAD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E3\u200E.\u200E8\u200E.\u200E2016 at 1:37 AM, SQUAD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe safe-deploy option for parachutes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was watching replay of \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.twitch.tv/ksptv/v/81795735\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESquadcast\u003C/a\u003E,\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis talking(time stamp-00:26:44),this feature was added back in 1.0.5 and is only possible to activate \u0022auto safe deployment\u0022 through .cfg file.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSince there is no line in \u0022Module Parachute\u0022 that can be changed to activate this behavior,i\u0027m asking what needs to be added?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EautoDeploy = True //??\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vorg","CreatedById":74652,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T20:32:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222706075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470429787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022brusura\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, brusura said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is very unfortunate, the ability to execute a maneuver node planned before the signal blackout is the foundation stone of mission without pilot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been stated there will be an option to crank it up so that you can get full signal loss.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NathanKell","CreatedById":75006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T22:01:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/81294-sebizzr/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002281294\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/81294-sebizzr/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sebi.zzr\u003C/a\u003E I\u0027ve said on other threads, but to repeat here, in the MODULE that is the ModuleParachute,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nautomateSafeDeploy = 0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat will deploy on safe. If you want Risky, use = 1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57899-brusura/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257899\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57899-brusura/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@brusura\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E includes a \u0027point at node\u0027 option, does it not? So there you go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-06T22:11:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthank you very much\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}